:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/orgs"}},{"index":1,"author_association":"NONE","body":"@Mugen87  I have looked into this but its unfortunately too massive to call live on a running 60 fps application. I edited my post above, in some occasions it can happen that i need to create 50 or more sprites in a single frame (an RPG, where a lot of damage numbers could pop up at any time, or a zone with NPCs is loaded into the world and their name plates are created at the same time). \r\nSo working with a round-robin system of cached HTML elements that get freed up every frame works, but it still causes problems when materials are loaded that are not rendered instantly, for example a spriteText that is invisible until later.\r\nIs there a way to at least force materials to update on the next render call, even if they are set to .visible = false?","created_at":"2018-02-03T00:08:50.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/13233#issuecomment-362747458","id":362747458,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/13233","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM2Mjc0NzQ1OA==","updated_at":"2018-02-03T00:08:50.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/362747458","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/dekdevy\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/dekdevy\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/8524746?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/dekdevy","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/dekdevy\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/dekdevy","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/dekdevy\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjg1MjQ3NDY=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/dekdevy\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/dekdevy\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/dekdevy\/starred{\/own